06/04/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- More than 100 houses were raided in various locations across Romania on Tuesday (April 6th) as part of a co-ordinated action by the Romanian, US and Czech police against internet fraud. 
The police busted three groups suspected of being involved in fraudulent internet sales of yachts, luxurious products and real estate property. 
Most of their victims were citizens of the US, Ukraine and Denmark. 
The operation resulted in the arrest of at least 70 people. 
(Adevarul, Jurnalul National, Ziare, Cotidianul, Evenimentul Zilei, Makfax - 06/04/10)
